listening to Beach Boys music.

00:24:58.890 --> 00:25:00.459 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah.

00:25:00.459 --> 00:25:02.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, I guess,
that's pretty good.

00:25:02.250 --> 00:25:04.390 align:middle line:90%
I like the music too.

00:25:04.390 --> 00:25:06.500 align:middle line:90%
But it's fun.

00:25:06.500 --> 00:25:08.211 align:middle line:90%
Some of these movies are fun.

00:25:08.211 --> 00:25:09.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They're
fun and they're good

00:25:09.960 --> 00:25:13.801 align:middle line:84%
and they're entertaining
and all of that.

00:25:13.801 --> 00:25:16.300 align:middle line:84%
The other one that, of course,
I really love is "Star Man"--

00:25:16.300 --> 00:25:17.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Tell me about that.

00:25:17.020 --> 00:25:18.655 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO:
--with Jeff Bridges.

00:25:18.655 --> 00:25:20.080 align:middle line:90%
I think it's just amazing.

00:25:20.080 --> 00:25:20.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He kind of
came down, right?

00:25:20.970 --> 00:25:22.095 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: He came down.

00:25:22.095 --> 00:25:27.220 align:middle line:84%
But Karen Allen represents
us, Earth people, and how

00:25:27.220 --> 00:25:29.920 align:middle line:90%
she was just engrossed in fear.

00:25:29.920 --> 00:25:32.610 align:middle line:84%
And as she did the journey
with him and discovered who

00:25:32.610 --> 00:25:34.000 align:middle line:90%
he really was on the inside--

00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:34.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: She fell
in love with him.

00:25:34.830 --> 00:25:36.496 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: She
fell in love with him.

00:25:36.496 --> 00:25:38.600 align:middle line:84%
And then, by the end,
she's helping him.

00:25:38.600 --> 00:25:39.670 align:middle line:90%
And she's embracing him.

00:25:39.670 --> 00:25:43.170 align:middle line:84%
And she joins with him and
ends up being pregnant.

00:25:43.170 --> 00:25:46.517 align:middle line:84%
And we've never had a
sequel to see what happens!

00:25:46.517 --> 00:25:47.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Where's the baby?

00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:48.891 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Where's the baby?

00:25:48.891 --> 00:25:50.100 align:middle line:90%
Where's the baby?

00:25:50.100 --> 00:25:51.800 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
it about Hollywood

00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:55.254 align:middle line:84%
and the messages of
extraterrestrial life?

00:25:55.254 --> 00:25:56.670 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well,
Hollywood will

00:25:56.670 --> 00:25:57.950 align:middle line:90%
do anything that makes money.

00:25:57.950 --> 00:25:58.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of course.

00:25:58.150 --> 00:25:59.608 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: So
that's why I think

00:25:59.608 --> 00:26:02.730 align:middle line:84%
we do see a lot of things
that are more negative-based.

00:26:02.730 --> 00:26:05.847 align:middle line:84%
Because they're always
doing the conflict and--

00:26:05.847 --> 00:26:06.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: People like that.

00:26:06.930 --> 00:26:10.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: --aliens are
going to eat you and things

00:26:10.200 --> 00:26:11.080 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:15.111 align:middle line:84%
I know, when I was a boy,
I loved horror films.

00:26:15.111 --> 00:26:16.860 align:middle line:84%
My niece and nephew,
when they were young,

00:26:16.860 --> 00:26:18.060 align:middle line:90%
they loved horror films.

00:26:18.060 --> 00:26:19.820 align:middle line:90%
And the gorier the better.

00:26:19.820 --> 00:26:22.850 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
it is in our nature.

00:26:22.850 --> 00:26:25.940 align:middle line:84%
But then, later on,
we start to want

00:26:25.940 --> 00:26:31.150 align:middle line:84%
to see things of-- what's
interesting is, like,

00:26:31.150 --> 00:26:32.660 align:middle line:84%
"Stranger at the
Pentagon," these

00:26:32.660 --> 00:26:35.330 align:middle line:84%
are things that are
now becoming inspired

00:26:35.330 --> 00:26:37.220 align:middle line:84%
by true stories, things
that are out there,

00:26:37.220 --> 00:26:38.890 align:middle line:84%
things that are
different, instead

00:26:38.890 --> 00:26:40.260 align:middle line:90%
of us seeing everything.

00:26:40.260 --> 00:26:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think the great
thing about "Star Trek"

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:46.550 align:middle line:84%
is that it's conditioned
everybody for life

00:26:46.550 --> 00:26:48.330 align:middle line:90%
out there in the universe.

00:26:48.330 --> 00:26:51.150 align:middle line:84%
And here's one of the most
interesting, coolest things

00:26:51.150 --> 00:26:54.120 align:middle line:84%
ever-- Gene
Roddenberry was trying

00:26:54.120 --> 00:26:55.811 align:middle line:90%
to sell that series everywhere.

00:26:55.811 --> 00:26:57.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And nobody wanted it.

00:26:57.060 --> 00:26:58.518 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And
nobody wanted it.

00:26:58.518 --> 00:27:02.150 align:middle line:90%
And he took it to Desilu.

00:27:02.150 --> 00:27:05.600 align:middle line:84%
And Lucille Ball, at that
time, was the president,

00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:10.030 align:middle line:84%
because Ricky-- or
Desi-- had stepped away.

00:27:10.030 --> 00:27:13.439 align:middle line:84%
And she is the one who
green lit "Star Trek."

00:27:13.439 --> 00:27:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow!

00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:15.570 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: We would
not have "Star Trek"

00:27:15.570 --> 00:27:16.130 align:middle line:90%
if it wasn't for Lucy.

00:27:16.130 --> 00:27:16.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Isn't that amazing?

00:27:16.820 --> 00:27:18.550 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And she also
did "Mission Impossible."

00:27:18.550 --> 00:27:20.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, that is amazing.

00:27:20.010 --> 00:27:21.544 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Isn't
that incredible?

00:27:21.544 --> 00:27:22.460 align:middle line:90%
So I really love Lucy.

00:27:22.460 --> 00:27:24.376 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Didn't Rod
Serling have the same kind

00:27:24.376 --> 00:27:27.246 align:middle line:84%
of battle trying to pitch
his idea for "Twilight Zone"?

00:27:27.246 --> 00:27:28.245 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes, yeah.

00:27:28.245 --> 00:27:30.110 align:middle line:90%
And look at what a-- man--

00:27:30.110 --> 00:27:33.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And in those
days, pitches were merely

00:27:33.160 --> 00:27:34.617 align:middle line:90%
meetings with executives.

00:27:34.617 --> 00:27:35.950 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes, that's right.

00:27:35.950 --> 00:27:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You didn't
have sizzle reels.

00:27:37.340 --> 00:27:37.630 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: No.

00:27:37.630 --> 00:27:39.088 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now you
have to have that.

00:27:39.088 --> 00:27:40.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Now
you have to have it.

00:27:40.690 --> 00:27:42.460 align:middle line:84%
When George Lucas
did "Star Wars,"

00:27:42.460 --> 00:27:45.300 align:middle line:84%
he was trying to explain
it to the Fox execs.

00:27:45.300 --> 00:27:47.530 align:middle line:84%
They had no clue what
he was trying to do,

00:27:47.530 --> 00:27:50.840 align:middle line:84%
what he was trying to
say, what his vision was.

00:27:50.840 --> 00:27:53.250 align:middle line:84%
And so, he actually
had to go out and hire

00:27:53.250 --> 00:27:56.990 align:middle line:84%
a professional
airbrush artist, who

00:27:56.990 --> 00:28:00.160 align:middle line:84%
came in and made giant
landscape pictures

00:28:00.160 --> 00:28:04.220 align:middle line:84%
this big of what it
was going to look like.

00:28:04.220 --> 00:28:05.152 align:middle line:90%
And that's how--

00:28:05.152 --> 00:28:06.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's what sold it.

00:28:06.360 --> 00:28:07.776 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO:
That's what sold it.

00:28:07.776 --> 00:28:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And nowadays, since we can make
sizzle reels or short films,

00:28:12.760 --> 00:28:15.680 align:middle line:84%
it gives them the idea of
what it will look like,

00:28:15.680 --> 00:28:17.260 align:middle line:90%
what it'll feel like.

00:28:17.260 --> 00:28:19.767 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Then you
have some bad aliens.

00:28:19.767 --> 00:28:20.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Right, yeah.

00:28:20.850 --> 00:28:23.496 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Like the movie
"Independence Day."

00:28:23.496 --> 00:28:24.488 align:middle line:90%


00:28:24.488 --> 00:28:26.472 align:middle line:90%
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

00:28:26.472 --> 00:28:27.960 align:middle line:90%
[RATTLING]

00:28:27.960 --> 00:28:29.450 align:middle line:90%
>>Is that an earthquake?

00:28:29.450 --> 00:28:31.762 align:middle line:84%
>>Let's just get there,
as quickly as possible.

00:28:31.762 --> 00:28:32.720 align:middle line:90%
>>What's the rush, huh?

00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:34.095 align:middle line:84%
You think we'll
get to Washington

00:28:34.095 --> 00:28:36.682 align:middle line:90%
and it won't be there?

00:28:36.682 --> 00:28:38.158 align:middle line:90%
>>It is confirmed.

00:28:38.158 --> 00:28:41.590 align:middle line:84%
The unexplained phenomenon
is headed for Moscow.

00:28:41.590 --> 00:28:42.610 align:middle line:90%
>>It's like in chess.

00:28:42.610 --> 00:28:44.460 align:middle line:84%
First, they're positioning their
pieces, using this one signal

00:28:44.460 --> 00:28:45.950 align:middle line:90%
to synchronize their efforts.

00:28:45.950 --> 00:28:47.370 align:middle line:90%
>>And then what?

00:28:47.370 --> 00:28:47.870 align:middle line:90%
>>Checkmate.

00:28:47.870 --> 00:28:48.822 align:middle line:90%


00:28:48.822 --> 00:28:50.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's also one
of my favorite movies.

00:28:50.780 --> 00:28:51.445 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes, mine too.

00:28:51.445 --> 00:28:52.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just loved it.

00:28:52.050 --> 00:28:53.008 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Mine too.

00:28:53.008 --> 00:28:55.270 align:middle line:84%
And they're making
"Independence Day II" right now.

00:28:55.270 --> 00:28:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Same people?

00:28:55.630 --> 00:28:56.365 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They're
actually shooting it.

00:28:56.365 --> 00:28:57.070 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Same characters?

00:28:57.070 --> 00:28:57.760 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Same characters.

00:28:57.760 --> 00:28:59.310 align:middle line:84%
But Will Smith's
not in it, I hear.

00:28:59.310 --> 00:29:00.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, he's
got to be in it!

00:29:00.180 --> 00:29:02.679 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah, but I know
Vivica Fox is because I just

00:29:02.679 --> 00:29:04.220 align:middle line:84%
tried to hire her
for a movie, and we

00:29:04.220 --> 00:29:05.080 align:middle line:90%
couldn't work out the dates.

00:29:05.080 --> 00:29:05.580 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:29:05.580 --> 00:29:07.565 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As a casting
director, would you

00:29:07.565 --> 00:29:09.927 align:middle line:84%
have insisted that Will
Smith be in that movie?

00:29:09.927 --> 00:29:11.760 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well, it
wouldn't be up to me.

00:29:11.760 --> 00:29:13.780 align:middle line:84%
Because that's a big
giant studio movie.

00:29:13.780 --> 00:29:16.080 align:middle line:84%
So it would be up
to-- and I don't

00:29:16.080 --> 00:29:19.100 align:middle line:84%
know what the reasoning
is that he's not in it.

00:29:19.100 --> 00:29:20.350 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it was his choice.

00:29:20.350 --> 00:29:21.800 align:middle line:90%
Or maybe he was unavailable.

00:29:21.800 --> 00:29:22.670 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:29:22.670 --> 00:29:24.878 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: "District Nine"--
let's take a look at that.

00:29:24.878 --> 00:29:25.520 align:middle line:90%


00:29:25.520 --> 00:29:26.580 align:middle line:90%
>>They don't belong here.

00:29:26.580 --> 00:29:28.954 align:middle line:84%
>>They're spending so much
money to keep them here,

00:29:28.954 --> 00:29:31.310 align:middle line:84%
when they could be spending
it on other things.

00:29:31.310 --> 00:29:33.310 align:middle line:84%
At least, they're keeping
them separate from us.

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:36.214 align:middle line:90%


00:29:36.214 --> 00:29:38.100 align:middle line:84%
>>A lot of bad things
started to happen.

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:39.204 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:29:39.204 --> 00:29:39.990 align:middle line:90%


00:29:39.990 --> 00:29:40.955 align:middle line:90%
>>They must just go.

00:29:40.955 --> 00:29:42.080 align:middle line:90%
I don't know where they go.

00:29:42.080 --> 00:29:43.672 align:middle line:90%
But they must just go.

00:29:43.672 --> 00:29:46.075 align:middle line:90%
>>We're at the breaking point.

00:29:46.075 --> 00:29:47.330 align:middle line:90%
People are living in fear.

00:29:47.330 --> 00:29:52.930 align:middle line:90%


00:29:52.930 --> 00:29:55.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, what about
that kind of a movie?

00:29:55.410 --> 00:29:57.493 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well, that's
a whole different take.

00:29:57.493 --> 00:30:00.770 align:middle line:84%
That's man making
aliens refugees

00:30:00.770 --> 00:30:01.945 align:middle line:90%
on the planet with these--

00:30:01.945 --> 00:30:02.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The little prawns.

00:30:02.510 --> 00:30:03.370 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Right.

00:30:03.370 --> 00:30:07.620 align:middle line:84%
The little prawns and
that kind of thing.

00:30:07.620 --> 00:30:10.140 align:middle line:84%
Which was a whole different
take on everything.

00:30:10.140 --> 00:30:15.870 align:middle line:84%
And with the giant ships hanging
in the air and all of that--

00:30:15.870 --> 00:30:18.034 align:middle line:84%
so again, it was a
controlling mechanism.

00:30:18.034 --> 00:30:20.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who comes up with
these great ideas, Craig,

00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:22.231 align:middle line:90%
in Hollywood?

00:30:22.231 --> 00:30:25.530 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: I think
an idea comes to you.

00:30:25.530 --> 00:30:27.530 align:middle line:84%
I know when I
write, an idea comes

00:30:27.530 --> 00:30:31.100 align:middle line:84%
and you just start
expanding upon it.

00:30:31.100 --> 00:30:35.810 align:middle line:84%
"Total Recall" was one
of the greatest ideas,

00:30:35.810 --> 00:30:39.760 align:middle line:84%
you know, the original that
Arnold Schwarzenegger was in.

00:30:39.760 --> 00:30:41.060 align:middle line:90%
Ron Shusett did that.

00:30:41.060 --> 00:30:47.050 align:middle line:84%
He also created "Predator"
and "Aliens vs. Predator."

00:30:47.050 --> 00:30:48.760 align:middle line:90%
I loved "Aliens vs. Predator."

00:30:48.760 --> 00:30:51.079 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I love
those movies, I do.

00:30:51.079 --> 00:30:52.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And they live forever.

00:30:52.370 --> 00:30:53.703 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They live forever.

00:30:53.703 --> 00:30:55.070 align:middle line:90%
And they're good.

00:30:55.070 --> 00:31:00.270 align:middle line:84%
But I also do agree, we need
more positive movies, as well,

00:31:00.270 --> 00:31:00.980 align:middle line:90%
about that.

00:31:00.980 --> 00:31:05.820 align:middle line:84%
And I actually belong to a group
in Hollywood of filmmakers,

00:31:05.820 --> 00:31:07.190 align:middle line:90%
where we all get together.

00:31:07.190 --> 00:31:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And we discuss and
we help each other

00:31:09.210 --> 00:31:12.920 align:middle line:84%
to try and get things
brought more into the light

00:31:12.920 --> 00:31:15.940 align:middle line:84%
and out in Hollywood,
in television and film.

00:31:15.940 --> 00:31:18.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: One of my favorites is
well-- I've got a lot of them--

00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:20.926 align:middle line:90%
is the movie "The Abyss."

00:31:20.926 --> 00:31:21.650 align:middle line:90%


00:31:21.650 --> 00:31:24.602 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:24.602 --> 00:31:50.387 align:middle line:90%


00:31:50.387 --> 00:31:52.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'll always
remember that part too,

00:31:52.220 --> 00:31:54.770 align:middle line:84%
where he's typing
back to his girlfriend

00:31:54.770 --> 00:31:59.110 align:middle line:84%
while he's down there, going,
I knew it was a one way trip.

00:31:59.110 --> 00:32:00.107 align:middle line:90%
Just a classic.

00:32:00.107 --> 00:32:00.815 align:middle line:90%
But he was saved!

00:32:00.815 --> 00:32:02.356 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah,
but he was saved.

00:32:02.356 --> 00:32:05.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Saved by the ETs.

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:07.355 align:middle line:90%
Brought him in and-- classic.

00:32:07.355 --> 00:32:08.605 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah, Ed Harris.

00:32:08.605 --> 00:32:09.104 align:middle line:90%
Love him.

00:32:09.104 --> 00:32:09.690 align:middle line:90%
He was great.

00:32:09.690 --> 00:32:13.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I've been a big
fan of submerged UFO cases.

00:32:13.060 --> 00:32:13.810 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes.

00:32:13.810 --> 00:32:15.768 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's something
going on down there.

00:32:15.768 --> 00:32:16.750 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah.

00:32:16.750 --> 00:32:18.666 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So as you look
at all of this, Craig,

00:32:18.666 --> 00:32:23.010 align:middle line:84%
and specifically your work with
"Stranger at the Pentagon,"

00:32:23.010 --> 00:32:28.310 align:middle line:84%
if this becomes a big
movie, will the short clip--

00:32:28.310 --> 00:32:29.430 align:middle line:90%
is that a standalone?

00:32:29.430 --> 00:32:31.522 align:middle line:84%
Or you think you have
to have the big movie?

00:32:31.522 --> 00:32:32.230 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: No.

00:32:32.230 --> 00:32:34.182 align:middle line:90%
The big movie has to be.

00:32:34.182 --> 00:32:35.640 align:middle line:84%
There's so much
more to this story.

00:32:35.640 --> 00:32:37.348 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would it look
anything like what

00:32:37.348 --> 00:32:38.570 align:middle line:90%
the smaller version was?

00:32:38.570 --> 00:32:43.430 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well, those
are scenes from the big film.

00:32:43.430 --> 00:32:46.530 align:middle line:84%
They're shortened
scenes that are taken

00:32:46.530 --> 00:32:48.410 align:middle line:90%
from the actual feature film.

00:32:48.410 --> 00:32:52.237 align:middle line:84%
And then, I ended it with a
cliffhanger in the short film.

00:32:52.237 --> 00:32:53.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Which you
could still change.

00:32:53.820 --> 00:32:55.695 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Which I
could-- right, exactly.

00:32:55.695 --> 00:32:59.634 align:middle line:84%
But the exciting thing is
that there's much information.

00:32:59.634 --> 00:33:02.050 align:middle line:84%
And there's so much of what
went on during the three years

00:33:02.050 --> 00:33:03.350 align:middle line:90%
that he was there.

00:33:03.350 --> 00:33:05.720 align:middle line:90%
And what he had to endure.

00:33:05.720 --> 00:33:10.920 align:middle line:84%
And Eisenhower and Nixon were
actually for his proposal.

00:33:10.920 --> 00:33:16.400 align:middle line:84%
But it was the constant
battle with the Joint Chiefs,

00:33:16.400 --> 00:33:20.090 align:middle line:90%
with the CIA and--

00:33:20.090 --> 00:33:21.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, what
did Thor want to do?

00:33:21.780 --> 00:33:23.680 align:middle line:90%
What was that proposal?

00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well,
the proposal that stood

00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:32.330 align:middle line:84%
alone was to help eliminate
sickness, disease, and poverty,

00:33:32.330 --> 00:33:33.700 align:middle line:90%
and to prolong life.

00:33:33.700 --> 00:33:35.919 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, but that means
businesses could go out

00:33:35.919 --> 00:33:36.710 align:middle line:90%
of business, right?

00:33:36.710 --> 00:33:38.251 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And
that's exactly what

00:33:38.251 --> 00:33:40.050 align:middle line:90%
they came back with in the end.

00:33:40.050 --> 00:33:42.720 align:middle line:84%
It would get rid of
pharmaceutical companies.

00:33:42.720 --> 00:33:45.870 align:middle line:84%
It would get rid of doctors,
nurses, all of that.

00:33:45.870 --> 00:33:48.310 align:middle line:90%
But then, you think about it.

00:33:48.310 --> 00:33:50.684 align:middle line:84%
This world's based on
monetary and greed.

00:33:50.684 --> 00:33:51.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:53.420 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: So if
all of that went away,

00:33:53.420 --> 00:33:56.220 align:middle line:84%
then greed would have
to go away, right?

00:33:56.220 --> 00:34:00.120 align:middle line:84%
In their society,
everybody is the same,

00:34:00.120 --> 00:34:04.960 align:middle line:84%
and everybody is taking care
of, and everybody is cared for,

00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:07.510 align:middle line:84%
and everybody does all
different kinds of jobs.

00:34:07.510 --> 00:34:09.560 align:middle line:84%
But they also live
very long lifespans.

00:34:09.560 --> 00:34:14.690 align:middle line:84%
So they aren't considered
an adult until they're 75.

00:34:14.690 --> 00:34:16.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, why didn't
people like Eisenhower

00:34:16.870 --> 00:34:19.870 align:middle line:84%
fight and say, we're
going to do this?

00:34:19.870 --> 00:34:21.810 align:middle line:90%
We're going to implement this?

00:34:21.810 --> 00:34:24.469 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take this
plan and make it happen

00:34:24.469 --> 00:34:25.989 align:middle line:90%
and make this a better planet?

00:34:25.989 --> 00:34:27.040 align:middle line:90%
Why not do that?

00:34:27.040 --> 00:34:29.110 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well,
I'm not exactly

00:34:29.110 --> 00:34:34.192 align:middle line:84%
sure of every little detail
that happened during that.

00:34:34.192 --> 00:34:35.650 align:middle line:84%
But there was a
lot of other things

00:34:35.650 --> 00:34:37.639 align:middle line:84%
that I know that
he was busy with.

00:34:37.639 --> 00:34:43.219 align:middle line:84%
And Dr. Frank told
me that he really

00:34:43.219 --> 00:34:48.730 align:middle line:84%
had befriended Richard Nixon as
well, because he was a lot more

00:34:48.730 --> 00:34:50.400 align:middle line:90%
available and accessible.

00:34:50.400 --> 00:34:52.719 align:middle line:84%
But that they really
did want this to happen.

00:34:52.719 --> 00:34:55.739 align:middle line:84%
And they were really
trying to help it.

00:34:55.739 --> 00:35:01.130 align:middle line:84%
Because they really did want
to help the American people.

00:35:01.130 --> 00:35:05.250 align:middle line:84%
Eisenhower really,
really talked about a lot

00:35:05.250 --> 00:35:09.360 align:middle line:84%
of stuff about the military
complex and all of that.

00:35:09.360 --> 00:35:11.942 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it was amazing.

00:35:11.942 --> 00:35:13.900 align:middle line:84%
I think I even have a
little quote that he did.

00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:15.560 align:middle line:90%
I'll use my cheat sheet.

00:35:15.560 --> 00:35:17.970 align:middle line:84%
He said, "I like to believe
that people, in the long run,

00:35:17.970 --> 00:35:21.420 align:middle line:84%
are going to do more to promote
peace than our governments.

00:35:21.420 --> 00:35:24.426 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, I think that
people want peace so much

00:35:24.426 --> 00:35:26.050 align:middle line:84%
that, one of these
days, the government

00:35:26.050 --> 00:35:28.140 align:middle line:84%
had better get out of the
way and let them have it."

00:35:28.140 --> 00:35:28.765 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:35:28.765 --> 00:35:30.900 align:middle line:84%
And he also said
in his departure,

00:35:30.900 --> 00:35:34.204 align:middle line:84%
be wary of the military
industrial complex.

00:35:34.204 --> 00:35:35.120 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Complex.

00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:35.630 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:35:35.630 --> 00:35:36.463 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He knew it.

00:35:36.463 --> 00:35:37.010 align:middle line:90%
He saw it.

00:35:37.010 --> 00:35:38.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's what's
happening right now.

00:35:38.480 --> 00:35:39.229 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes.

00:35:39.229 --> 00:35:41.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Richard
Nixon, apparently,

00:35:41.400 --> 00:35:46.030 align:middle line:84%
saw extraterrestrials
at Homestead Military

00:35:46.030 --> 00:35:49.300 align:middle line:84%
Base down in Florida and brought
Jackie Gleason to see them.

00:35:49.300 --> 00:35:50.530 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: That's correct.

00:35:50.530 --> 00:35:52.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And apparently,
Jackie Gleason's

00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:54.610 align:middle line:84%
life changed for the
rest of his life.

00:35:54.610 --> 00:35:56.880 align:middle line:90%
He was always interested in ETs.

00:35:56.880 --> 00:36:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And this just scared
him, mind-boggled him.

00:36:00.470 --> 00:36:02.059 align:middle line:90%
It did whatever it had to do.

00:36:02.059 --> 00:36:02.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah.

00:36:02.850 --> 00:36:04.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But Nixon
was in on this stuff.

00:36:04.090 --> 00:36:05.339 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: He was in on it.

00:36:05.339 --> 00:36:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And I even heard,
throughout the grapevine,

00:36:08.470 --> 00:36:11.810 align:middle line:84%
that when Spielberg made "Close
Encounters" that he was taken

00:36:11.810 --> 00:36:13.710 align:middle line:90%
and shown the beings as well.

00:36:13.710 --> 00:36:15.169 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That would
be fascinating.

00:36:15.169 --> 00:36:16.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Wouldn't
that be fascinating?

00:36:16.960 --> 00:36:18.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How would
you react to that?

00:36:18.840 --> 00:36:19.590 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Wow!

00:36:19.590 --> 00:36:22.610 align:middle line:84%
Just to see them, if you
were brought, and saw them--

00:36:22.610 --> 00:36:24.105 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Would it be eerie?

00:36:24.105 --> 00:36:26.104 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: I don't
know if it would be eerie.

00:36:26.104 --> 00:36:28.190 align:middle line:84%
I think it'd be, well,
definitely otherworldly.

00:36:28.190 --> 00:36:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And it would
definitely be something

00:36:29.810 --> 00:36:31.380 align:middle line:84%
that would stay with you
the rest of your life.

00:36:31.380 --> 00:36:32.546 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Would it scare you?

00:36:32.546 --> 00:36:34.856 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: It
wouldn't scare me.

00:36:34.856 --> 00:36:36.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: If you saw big heads--

00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:37.640 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Big
heads and big eyes.

00:36:37.640 --> 00:36:38.556 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --black eyes.

00:36:38.556 --> 00:36:40.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO:
Well, they're dead.

00:36:40.050 --> 00:36:40.350 align:middle line:90%
They're not alive.

00:36:40.350 --> 00:36:41.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Spiney hands.

00:36:41.480 --> 00:36:43.865 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They're not alive.

00:36:43.865 --> 00:36:46.324 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But you wonder whether
they were good ETs, or not.

00:36:46.324 --> 00:36:47.698 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Or
if they weren't.

00:36:47.698 --> 00:36:48.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:36:48.660 --> 00:36:49.910 align:middle line:90%
And that I don't know.

00:36:49.910 --> 00:36:50.660 align:middle line:90%
That I don't know.

00:36:50.660 --> 00:36:52.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, the
universe is so vast.

00:36:52.420 --> 00:36:53.509 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah.

00:36:53.509 --> 00:36:55.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
the message you want

00:36:55.050 --> 00:36:59.232 align:middle line:84%
people to get when they watch
"Stranger at the Pentagon"?

00:36:59.232 --> 00:37:01.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: That there is
life out there in the universe.

00:37:01.690 --> 00:37:06.210 align:middle line:84%
And that that life is
here helping us in ways

00:37:06.210 --> 00:37:12.100 align:middle line:84%
that we couldn't even
understand-- planetary-wise,

00:37:12.100 --> 00:37:14.690 align:middle line:90%
spiritually.

00:37:14.690 --> 00:37:20.660 align:middle line:84%
And helping us to live a more
enriched spiritual life as

00:37:20.660 --> 00:37:23.870 align:middle line:84%
well, through all of
the different contacts

00:37:23.870 --> 00:37:25.760 align:middle line:84%
and through all of
the information that's

00:37:25.760 --> 00:37:28.750 align:middle line:84%
being imparted and
brought into the world.

00:37:28.750 --> 00:37:31.370 align:middle line:84%
We know that over the
past 30, 40 years,

00:37:31.370 --> 00:37:35.860 align:middle line:84%
we've had a major giant spike
in spiritualism on the planet.

00:37:35.860 --> 00:37:36.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huge.

00:37:36.570 --> 00:37:38.110 align:middle line:90%
Not necessarily religion.

00:37:38.110 --> 00:37:40.380 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Not
religious, but people

00:37:40.380 --> 00:37:44.620 align:middle line:84%
really believing in spirituality
and wanting to make themself

00:37:44.620 --> 00:37:45.120 align:middle line:90%
grow.

00:37:45.120 --> 00:37:50.600 align:middle line:84%
So what people are now doing
is, instead of using their mind,

00:37:50.600 --> 00:37:52.830 align:middle line:84%
they use their heart
to rule their mind.

00:37:52.830 --> 00:37:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And that's when you
stop thinking about,

00:37:56.080 --> 00:37:57.230 align:middle line:90%
what's best for me?

00:37:57.230 --> 00:38:00.910 align:middle line:84%
What can I do for me to
better get what I want?

00:38:00.910 --> 00:38:03.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, it's to help,
not only mankind,

00:38:03.520 --> 00:38:04.650 align:middle line:90%
but all universal kind.

00:38:04.650 --> 00:38:07.340 align:middle line:84%
And they look at it from
that way, Valiant Thor

00:38:07.340 --> 00:38:08.812 align:middle line:90%
and that whole complement.

00:38:08.812 --> 00:38:10.270 align:middle line:84%
They look at it
from the standpoint

00:38:10.270 --> 00:38:14.460 align:middle line:84%
that they are here to help
all of universal-kind,

00:38:14.460 --> 00:38:17.010 align:middle line:84%
because they are all
of universal-kind.

00:38:17.010 --> 00:38:17.820 align:middle line:90%
And they know that.

00:38:17.820 --> 00:38:18.861 align:middle line:90%
And they understand that.

00:38:18.861 --> 00:38:20.850 align:middle line:84%
So they're waiting
for us to catch up.

00:38:20.850 --> 00:38:23.585 align:middle line:84%
And when that day comes
and we rejoin with--

00:38:23.585 --> 00:38:24.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it will.

00:38:24.460 --> 00:38:25.543 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And it will.

00:38:25.543 --> 00:38:26.600 align:middle line:90%
It's got to.

00:38:26.600 --> 00:38:28.870 align:middle line:90%
There's so many sightings.

00:38:28.870 --> 00:38:32.100 align:middle line:84%
There's so much stuff
that's going on.

00:38:32.100 --> 00:38:34.470 align:middle line:84%
And we hear new
things every day.

00:38:34.470 --> 00:38:36.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They could be
Valiant Thor's ships.

00:38:36.500 --> 00:38:37.666 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They could be.

00:38:37.666 --> 00:38:39.124 align:middle line:90%
They absolutely could be.

00:38:39.124 --> 00:38:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Which is
interesting too.

00:38:40.540 --> 00:38:42.930 align:middle line:84%
Here's another
thing-- the shroud

00:38:42.930 --> 00:38:49.610 align:middle line:84%
of secrecy that occurred
in '57-- why hasn't he

00:38:49.610 --> 00:38:51.610 align:middle line:90%
made himself more known today?

00:38:51.610 --> 00:38:55.950 align:middle line:84%
There's something going
on, which is preventing him

00:38:55.950 --> 00:38:58.397 align:middle line:90%
from simply saying, I'm here.

00:38:58.397 --> 00:38:59.230 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Right.

00:38:59.230 --> 00:38:59.650 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:38:59.650 --> 00:39:01.024 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do
you think it is?

00:39:01.024 --> 00:39:03.150 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Well,
back in those days,

00:39:03.150 --> 00:39:05.910 align:middle line:84%
they were more
accessible, the beings.

00:39:05.910 --> 00:39:07.170 align:middle line:90%
I know Valiant Thor was.

00:39:07.170 --> 00:39:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And actually, there's
been several people

00:39:09.170 --> 00:39:12.080 align:middle line:84%
that have come forward since
I've made the film who actually

00:39:12.080 --> 00:39:15.120 align:middle line:90%
met him back in the day.

00:39:15.120 --> 00:39:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And their description of him
and the feeling that they got

00:39:20.260 --> 00:39:21.550 align:middle line:90%
were all the same.

00:39:21.550 --> 00:39:23.270 align:middle line:90%
Two of them are women.

00:39:23.270 --> 00:39:24.740 align:middle line:84%
But the one thing
that both women

00:39:24.740 --> 00:39:26.680 align:middle line:84%
said-- which was
interesting-- is

00:39:26.680 --> 00:39:30.370 align:middle line:84%
that there was a
pheromone about him that

00:39:30.370 --> 00:39:33.990 align:middle line:90%
smelled like love and peace.

00:39:33.990 --> 00:39:35.095 align:middle line:90%
And you felt safe.

00:39:35.095 --> 00:39:35.845 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Goodness.

00:39:35.845 --> 00:39:37.520 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And
goodness and beauty.

00:39:37.520 --> 00:39:40.760 align:middle line:84%
And everybody feels
that when they meet him.

00:39:40.760 --> 00:39:45.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think that when they
turned his proposal down,

00:39:45.260 --> 00:39:48.000 align:middle line:84%
he turned to Dr.
Frank, who had happened

00:39:48.000 --> 00:39:52.090 align:middle line:84%
to have been in Washington
giving a lecture on UFOs

00:39:52.090 --> 00:39:53.140 align:middle line:90%
and the Bible.

00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:57.560 align:middle line:84%
And I think that he was
his grassroots campaign

00:39:57.560 --> 00:39:59.760 align:middle line:90%
to continue the story.

00:39:59.760 --> 00:40:01.780 align:middle line:90%
And Dr. Frank toured the world.

00:40:01.780 --> 00:40:04.751 align:middle line:84%
He used to go to Korea and
fill stadiums of people

00:40:04.751 --> 00:40:06.000 align:middle line:90%
who wanted to hear about this.

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:06.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: People were into this.

00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:06.800 align:middle line:90%
They still are.

00:40:06.800 --> 00:40:07.280 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: They still are.

00:40:07.280 --> 00:40:08.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But it was huge then.

00:40:08.540 --> 00:40:10.289 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: But it
was really huge then.

00:40:10.289 --> 00:40:13.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Was the
Valiant Thor visitation

00:40:13.940 --> 00:40:16.782 align:middle line:84%
the basis for the movie "The
Day the Earth Stood Still"?

00:40:16.782 --> 00:40:17.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: No.

00:40:17.490 --> 00:40:18.990 align:middle line:90%
Because that was made--

00:40:18.990 --> 00:40:20.240 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That came out before?

00:40:20.240 --> 00:40:22.100 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: That
came out in 1951.

00:40:22.100 --> 00:40:22.910 align:middle line:90%
And Valiant Thor--

00:40:22.910 --> 00:40:23.565 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: About six years before.

00:40:23.565 --> 00:40:25.080 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: --arrived in '57.

00:40:25.080 --> 00:40:28.110 align:middle line:84%
But there were probably
others before him as well.

00:40:28.110 --> 00:40:33.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, what do you think,
then, of that movie coming out

00:40:33.490 --> 00:40:36.710 align:middle line:84%
six years before almost the
exact same thing happened

00:40:36.710 --> 00:40:38.240 align:middle line:90%
in real life?

00:40:38.240 --> 00:40:38.885 align:middle line:90%
That's bizarre.

00:40:38.885 --> 00:40:39.718 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Right.

00:40:39.718 --> 00:40:43.410 align:middle line:84%
So it makes you wonder,
could somebody else like that

00:40:43.410 --> 00:40:45.062 align:middle line:90%
have come?

00:40:45.062 --> 00:40:46.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We have seen--

00:40:46.020 --> 00:40:49.140 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: And they
wanted to see what

00:40:49.140 --> 00:40:50.390 align:middle line:90%
the world's reaction would be.

00:40:50.390 --> 00:40:53.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We have seen
things happen in Hollywood,

00:40:53.170 --> 00:40:56.280 align:middle line:84%
like "The Lone Gunman,"
where it depicted

00:40:56.280 --> 00:40:59.170 align:middle line:90%
planes hitting tall buildings.

00:40:59.170 --> 00:41:02.600 align:middle line:90%
And then, 9/11 happens.

00:41:02.600 --> 00:41:06.370 align:middle line:84%
So you've got the movie "The
Day the Earth Stood Still."

00:41:06.370 --> 00:41:09.097 align:middle line:84%
And then, a real, so-called
"visitation" occurs.

00:41:09.097 --> 00:41:09.930 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Right.

00:41:09.930 --> 00:41:13.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why is Hollywood
so ahead of the curve?

00:41:13.330 --> 00:41:15.670 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO:
Well, I also think,

00:41:15.670 --> 00:41:18.215 align:middle line:84%
could those thoughts
be implanted?

00:41:18.215 --> 00:41:18.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Maybe.

00:41:18.840 --> 00:41:21.720 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Maybe Valiant
Thor implanted those thoughts

00:41:21.720 --> 00:41:25.352 align:middle line:84%
in a writer or Robert
Wise way back when.

00:41:25.352 --> 00:41:26.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or they're
told to do it--

00:41:26.810 --> 00:41:27.850 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Or
they're told to do it.

00:41:27.850 --> 00:41:29.058 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --by the government.

00:41:29.058 --> 00:41:30.150 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: That's true.

00:41:30.150 --> 00:41:32.510 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's so many
different scenarios

00:41:32.510 --> 00:41:33.740 align:middle line:90%
that could have happened.

00:41:33.740 --> 00:41:36.650 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure there
were other beings that

00:41:36.650 --> 00:41:39.390 align:middle line:90%
came before him as well.

00:41:39.390 --> 00:41:46.160 align:middle line:84%
But Eisenhower was somebody
who was really hands-on

00:41:46.160 --> 00:41:49.270 align:middle line:90%
with visitors, as we know.

00:41:49.270 --> 00:41:53.370 align:middle line:84%
Because he'd met with
many different visitors.

00:41:53.370 --> 00:41:56.610 align:middle line:84%
McElroy, the representative,
I think, from New Hampshire--

00:41:56.610 --> 00:41:58.760 align:middle line:84%
there's a whole
YouTube video of him

00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:01.800 align:middle line:84%
saying he saw the papers
on his desk of him

00:42:01.800 --> 00:42:03.700 align:middle line:84%
meeting with several
extraterrestrial races.

00:42:03.700 --> 00:42:04.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Isn't that amazing?

00:42:04.550 --> 00:42:05.480 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yes.

00:42:05.480 --> 00:42:06.350 align:middle line:90%
And that--

00:42:06.350 --> 00:42:07.603 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why would he
make this up, right?

00:42:07.603 --> 00:42:08.394 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPOBASSO: Yeah.

00:42:08.394 --> 00:42:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And that they were here
to promote peace, love,

00:42:10.660 --> 00:42:11.930 align:middle line:90%
and goodwill.

